data-triple-N3.o: "Eric Patrick Clapton, CBE, (born 30 March 1945) is an English musician, singer, songwriter and guitarist. He is the only three-time inductee to the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame: once as a solo artist, and separately as a member of The Yardbirds and Cream. Clapton has been referred to as one of the most important and influential guitarists of all time."@en
